            <scopecontent id="aspace_ce4feac68b42cdb2d18d0be7309713c3">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>This collection consists of a scrapbook kept by Caroline Suydam (Duer) McLanahan during the years 1893-1897. In the book are mounted invitations, calling cards, programs, dance cards, newspaper clippings, and other memorabilia relating to New Haven and New York City society, and to social events at Yale University. Daughter of Denning Duer of New Haven, Caroline S. Duer later married George X. McLanahan of the Yale class of 1896.</p>
            </scopecontent>
